	(2300,'keywords','17','{\"id\":17,\"value\":\"crossdimensionalrampage\",\"label\":\"Cross-Dimensional Rampage\",\"cardTypes\":[1,2,4,5],\"details\":[[\"As different Hulks rampage across planets and dimensions, only another Hulk can stop them!\"],{\"points\":[[\"\\u201cCross-Dimensional Hulk Rampage\\u201d means \",{\"bold\":\"\\u201cEach player reveals one of their Hulk Heroes or a Hulk card in their Victory Pile or gains a Wound.\\u201d\"}],[\"You can reveal any card that includes the word \\u201cHulk\\u201d in its card name, Hero name, Villain Group name, or Tactics for Hulk Masterminds. This includes any Red Hulk, She-Hulk, Red She-Hulk, Skaar, Son of Hulk, Joe Fixit Grey Hulk, Hulkling, Hulk Gang, Cosmic Hulk Robot, Hulkbuster, Enchain the Hulk, and so on.\"],[\"You don\\u2019t need to know the whole history of Marvel comics to judge who counts as a Hulk \\u2013 just rely on whether the card says Hulk in its name or not. There are only a few, very specific exceptions we have to make to stay true to the characters: \\u201cNul, Breaker of Worlds\\u201d from Fear Itself and \\u201cMaestro\\u201d (core set) count as Hulks for this.\"],[\"Some Heroes can transform into Hulks, like Bruce Banner and Amadeus Cho. A puny \\u201cBruce Banner\\u201d card doesn\\u2019t say \\u201cHulk\\u201d on it, so it can\\u2019t stop a Hulk Rampage. But revealing the transformed Bruce Banner card named \\u201cSavage Hulk Unleashed\\u201d works.\"],[\"When a Cross-Dimensional Hulk Rampage happens, you can choose to gain the Wound, even if you have a Hulk that you already played or could otherwise reveal. You might want the Wound if you have cards that benefit from gaining   Wounds, or a card that benefits from preventing Wounds.\"],[\"There are also Cross-Dimensional Void, Illuminati, Deadpool, Thor, Colossus, Zombie, Demon, Party, Ultron, and Wolverine (\\u201cWeapon X\\u201d and \\u201cOld Man Logan\\u201d included) Rampages.\"]]}],\"_id\":\"1xTIW7E3qbCwEc7f\",\"detailsOutput\":\"As different Hulks rampage across planets and dimensions, only another Hulk can stop them!<ul><li>\\u201cCross-Dimensional Hulk Rampage\\u201d means <strong>\\u201cEach player reveals one of their Hulk Heroes or a Hulk card in their Victory Pile or gains a Wound.\\u201d<\\/strong><\\/li><li>You can reveal any card that includes the word \\u201cHulk\\u201d in its card name, Hero name, Villain Group name, or Tactics for Hulk Masterminds. This includes any Red Hulk, She-Hulk, Red She-Hulk, Skaar, Son of Hulk, Joe Fixit Grey Hulk, Hulkling, Hulk Gang, Cosmic Hulk Robot, Hulkbuster, Enchain the Hulk, and so on.<\\/li><li>You don\\u2019t need to know the whole history of Marvel comics to judge who counts as a Hulk \\u2013 just rely on whether the card says Hulk in its name or not. There are only a few, very specific exceptions we have to make to stay true to the characters: \\u201cNul, Breaker of Worlds\\u201d from Fear Itself and \\u201cMaestro\\u201d (core set) count as Hulks for this.<\\/li><li>Some Heroes can transform into Hulks, like Bruce Banner and Amadeus Cho. A puny \\u201cBruce Banner\\u201d card doesn\\u2019t say \\u201cHulk\\u201d on it, so it can\\u2019t stop a Hulk Rampage. But revealing the transformed Bruce Banner card named \\u201cSavage Hulk Unleashed\\u201d works.<\\/li><li>When a Cross-Dimensional Hulk Rampage happens, you can choose to gain the Wound, even if you have a Hulk that you already played or could otherwise reveal. You might want the Wound if you have cards that benefit from gaining   Wounds, or a card that benefits from preventing Wounds.<\\/li><li>There are also Cross-Dimensional Void, Illuminati, Deadpool, Thor, Colossus, Zombie, Demon, Party, Ultron, and Wolverine (\\u201cWeapon X\\u201d and \\u201cOld Man Logan\\u201d included) Rampages.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}',0),
