	(2349,'keywords','54','{\"id\":54,\"value\":\"digest\",\"label\":\"Digest\",\"cardTypes\":[1],\"details\":[[\"This grisly keyword represents how the Venom and Carnage symbiotes get stronger as they devour people and absorb their energy.\"],{\"points\":[[\"Some Heroes say things like \\u201c\",{\"bold\":\"Digest 2\"},\": Draw a card.\\u201d \"],[{\"bold\":\"Use this Digest ability only if you have at least that many cards in your Victory Pile.\"}],[\"All kinds of cards in your Victory Pile count for Digest. This includes Henchman Villains, regular Villains, Bystanders, Mastermind Tactics, Traps from other sets, etc.\"],[\"You don\\u2019t have to remove any cards from your Victory Pile to use Digest.\"],[\"Even if you have 10 cards in your Victory Pile, you can\\u2019t use a card\\u2019s \\u201cDigest 2\\u201d ability five times \\u2013 just once.\"]]}],\"_id\":\"Y78J0IiWoZ8pIIgz\",\"detailsOutput\":\"This grisly keyword represents how the Venom and Carnage symbiotes get stronger as they devour people and absorb their energy.<ul><li>Some Heroes say things like \\u201c<strong>Digest 2<\\/strong>: Draw a card.\\u201d <\\/li><li><strong>Use this Digest ability only if you have at least that many cards in your Victory Pile.<\\/strong><\\/li><li>All kinds of cards in your Victory Pile count for Digest. This includes Henchman Villains, regular Villains, Bystanders, Mastermind Tactics, Traps from other sets, etc.<\\/li><li>You don\\u2019t have to remove any cards from your Victory Pile to use Digest.<\\/li><li>Even if you have 10 cards in your Victory Pile, you can\\u2019t use a card\\u2019s \\u201cDigest 2\\u201d ability five times \\u2013 just once.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}',0),
	(2350,'keywords','91','{\"id\":91,\"value\":\"whatif\",\"label\":\"What If...?\",\"cardTypes\":[1],\"details\":[[\"This new keyword highlights how a Hero\\u2019s destiny can pivot on a single crucial choice, with consequences that spill through the rest of that dimension. Some Hero cards say things like \\u201c\",{\"bold\":\"What If\\u2026?\"},\": You get \",{\"bold\":\"+3\"},{\"icon\":2},\".\\u201d\"],{\"points\":[[\"This means \",{\"bold\":\"\\u201cChoose a Hero Class or Hero Name. Then reveal the top card of your deck, and either put it back on top of your deck or discard it. If the revealed card had the Hero Class or Hero Name you chose, then do the What If effect.\\u201d\"}],[\"What If...? is not allowed to trigger on 0-cost grey starting cards like S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent or S.H.I.E.L.D. Trooper, so don\\u2019t choose those Hero Names.\"],[\"Even if a What If...? ability misses, it\\u2019s still valuable to be able to choose to put your top card in your discard pile or not. For example, it can give you key information about your top card so you know what to choose with your next What If...? card that turn. Or if the top card is a S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent, you can discard it so you have a chance to hit with your next What If...? ability that turn and so you don\\u2019t have to draw it next turn.\"],[\"If you choose a Hero Name like \\u201cBlack Widow,\\u201d that will trigger on any card whose Hero Name is literally \\u201cBlack Widow\\u201d as well as any Hero Name that contains \\u201cBlack Widow\\u201d, such as \\u201cApocalyptic Black Widow.\\u201d However, you have to choose an actual Hero Name. You can\\u2019t choose just the word \\u201cCaptain\\u201d and trigger on both Captain America and Captain Carter cards, since the single word \\u201cCaptain\\u201d isn\\u2019t a Hero Name.\"]]},[{\"bold\":\"Increasing Your Chances with What If...?\"}],[\"There are lots of ways you can increase the chance that your What If...? abilities will work:\"],{\"points\":[[\"First: There are several cards in this set that let you reveal the top card of your deck or put a card on top of your deck, so that you know what to choose with What If...?.\"],[\"Second: You can try focusing your deck on a single Hero Class or single Hero Name.\"],[\"Third: Collecting lots of What If...? cards can let you see the top card with the first What If...?, so you know what to guess with the rest of your What If...? abilities that turn.\"],[\"Fourth: You can look for ways to KO your 0-cost starter cards and avoid or KO Wounds.\"]]}],\"_id\":\"YPho6aJWyiyZYlRx\",\"detailsOutput\":\"This new keyword highlights how a Hero\\u2019s destiny can pivot on a single crucial choice, with consequences that spill through the rest of that dimension. Some Hero cards say things like \\u201c<strong>What If\\u2026?<\\/strong>: You get <strong>+3<\\/strong><img src=\\\"\\/images\\/icon\\/2.svg\\\"  width=\\\"30px\\\" height=\\\"15px\\\" style=\\\"object-fit: cover;\\\">.\\u201d<ul><li>This means <strong>\\u201cChoose a Hero Class or Hero Name. Then reveal the top card of your deck, and either put it back on top of your deck or discard it. If the revealed card had the Hero Class or Hero Name you chose, then do the What If effect.\\u201d<\\/strong><\\/li><li>What If...? is not allowed to trigger on 0-cost grey starting cards like S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent or S.H.I.E.L.D. Trooper, so don\\u2019t choose those Hero Names.<\\/li><li>Even if a What If...? ability misses, it\\u2019s still valuable to be able to choose to put your top card in your discard pile or not. For example, it can give you key information about your top card so you know what to choose with your next What If...? card that turn. Or if the top card is a S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent, you can discard it so you have a chance to hit with your next What If...? ability that turn and so you don\\u2019t have to draw it next turn.<\\/li><li>If you choose a Hero Name like \\u201cBlack Widow,\\u201d that will trigger on any card whose Hero Name is literally \\u201cBlack Widow\\u201d as well as any Hero Name that contains \\u201cBlack Widow\\u201d, such as \\u201cApocalyptic Black Widow.\\u201d However, you have to choose an actual Hero Name. You can\\u2019t choose just the word \\u201cCaptain\\u201d and trigger on both Captain America and Captain Carter cards, since the single word \\u201cCaptain\\u201d isn\\u2019t a Hero Name.<\\/li><\\/ul><strong>Increasing Your Chances with What If...?<\\/strong>There are lots of ways you can increase the chance that your What If...? abilities will work:<ul><li>First: There are several cards in this set that let you reveal the top card of your deck or put a card on top of your deck, so that you know what to choose with What If...?.<\\/li><li>Second: You can try focusing your deck on a single Hero Class or single Hero Name.<\\/li><li>Third: Collecting lots of What If...? cards can let you see the top card with the first What If...?, so you know what to guess with the rest of your What If...? abilities that turn.<\\/li><li>Fourth: You can look for ways to KO your 0-cost starter cards and avoid or KO Wounds.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}',0);
