ing <strong>1<\\/strong><img src=\\\"\\/images\\/icon\\/2.svg\\\"  width=\\\"30px\\\" height=\\\"15px\\\" style=\\\"object-fit: cover;\\\"> more than you need when recruiting a Hero.<ul><li>Some Heroes say things like \\u201c<strong>Excessive Kindness:<\\/strong> Draw a card.\\u201d<\\/li><li><strong>Once per turn, you can spend 1<\\/strong><img src=\\\"\\/images\\/icon\\/2.svg\\\"  width=\\\"30px\\\" height=\\\"15px\\\" style=\\\"object-fit: cover;\\\"><strong> more than you need to recruit a Hero \\u201cusing Excessive Kindness.\\u201d If you do, you get to use all the \\u201cExcessive Kindness abilities on cards you played this turn.<\\/strong><\\/li><li>Say you\\u2019ve played three Heroes with Excessive Kindness abilities this turn. If you spend <strong>8<\\/strong><img src=\\\"\\/images\\/icon\\/2.svg\\\"  width=\\\"30px\\\" height=\\\"15px\\\" style=\\\"object-fit: cover;\\\"> to recruit a Hero that has cost 7, then you\\u2019ll get to use all three Excessive Kindness abilities!<\\/li><li>If you don\\u2019t recruit anything this turn, or if you don\\u2019t spend an extra <strong>1<\\/strong><img src=\\\"\\/images\\/icon\\/2.svg\\\"  width=\\\"30px\\\" height=\\\"15px\\\" style=\\\"object-fit: cover;\\\"> on someone, then you won\\u2019t be able to use Excessive Kindness.<\\/li><li>Since you can only recruit \\u201cusing Excessive Kindness once per turn, you can only use a card\\u2019s Excessive Kindness ability once per turn. (It\\u2019s OK to play two cards with the same card name, recruit a Hero \\u201cusing Excessive Kindness and use both of those cards\\u2019 Excessive Kindness abilities.)<\\/li><li>If you recruit using Excessive Kindness and then draw or play more cards with Excessive Kindness abilities later in the turn, it will be too late to use those abilities.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}',0),
