	(2365,'keywords','68','{\"id\":68,\"value\":\"contestofchampions\",\"label\":\"Contest of Champions\",\"cardTypes\":[1,2,4,5],\"details\":[[\"The Grandmaster and the Elders of the Universe are literally immortal. To them, mortals are merely playthings. This is shown with the Contest of Champions keyword. Some Villains and Masterminds say things like \\u201cAmbush: Contest of Champions \",{\"hc\":4},\".\\u201d When this happens:\"],{\"points\":[[\"Each player in turn reveals a single card, either from their hand, or that they played this turn, or the top card of their deck. That player announces their \\u201cContest Score,\\u201d which is that card\\u2019s printed cost, doubled if it\\u2019s a \",{\"hc\":4},\" card.\"],[\"You must choose carefully whether to use the best score you have from your hand, or to take a risk by trying the top card of your deck instead.\"],[\"After all players have announced their Contest Score, then Evil tries to win the contest. Reveal the top two cards of the Hero Deck, and Evil uses whichever card gives the highest Contest Score \",{\"italic\":\"(taking account of any doubling)\"},\". Again, this is the card\\u2019s printed cost, doubled if it\\u2019s a \",{\"hc\":4},\" card. Then put both those cards on the bottom of the Hero Deck.\"],[\"Whichever score is highest (or tied for highest) \\u201cwins\\u201d the contest. Everyone else \\u201closes.\\u201d\"],[\"For example, in a 3-player game, say Alana\\u2019s score is 6, Piper\\u2019s score is 6, Melody\\u2019s score is 4, and Evil\\u2019s score is 6. Then Alana, Piper, and the Mastermind all win the contest, and Melody loses the contest.\"],[\"The card lists outcomes for winning & losing.\"],[\"A few cards reveal a Hero card and use its colors for a contest. This can create contests that are multicolor, such as \\u201cContest of Champions \",{\"hc\":5},\", \",{\"hc\":3},\".\\u201d In this case, any card that includes either \",{\"hc\":5},\" or \",{\"hc\":3},\" will match the contest an